The White House Press Secretary, Robert Gibbs, held a press briefing on January 20, 2011. During the briefing, he addressed a variety of topics, including President Obama's discussions with Chinese President Hu Jintao, the President's plans for reelection, and various policy issues such as healthcare reform and gun control. Gibbs also mentioned the President's upcoming State of the Union address and his visit to Schenectady, New York. He also discussed the administration's position on human rights in China, the war in Afghanistan, and the recent arrests of individuals in Canada for terrorism-related activities.